@node FUNCTION "Function"

   This program makes boxes with a text-box ander each of them, so you can print the name of the colour
   ther. I'm afraid ARexx is not able to colourize the boxes itself, as Wordworth doesn't support that
   (yet?). @{":-(" link Restrictions}
   For German users, there is a @{"file" link Document} made ready for WW 3.0.+.


@endnode
@node RESTRICTIONS "Restrictions"

   I'm sorry WW doesn't let you make coloured boxes with ARexx. This is why  you have to click on every
   box and tell WW which colour to take. For German users, there is a @{"WW-document" link document}. 

   You probably have to adapt a line in the script. If you have problems and the script doesn't work,
   do the following:
   1. Load the script with an editor or a word processor like WW
   2. Change the following line:
         Drawbox "1" 2+(hor*4.25)"cm" 1+((ver*4.16))"cm" "3.5cm" "3cm" TRANSPARENT "1pt" SCHWARZ SINGLELINE NONE "0.3cm"
      (this is quite near the bottom)
      Look out for "SCHWARZ" and replace it by "BLACK".
   3. Save it again. If you have used a word processor, save it as ASCII.

   If it still doesn't work, contact @{"me" link Autor}.
@endnode

@node DOCUMENT "document"

   For German users, there is a WW-document. But as the colours are saved in plain text, I doubt
   whether you can use that one with the English WW-version. Please tell me if you can!!

@endnode


